00:45.147 --> 00:46.748
Hey!

01:08.370 --> 01:10.705
(chimes, vibrate

01:14.810 --> 01:16.411
Charlotte?
Who's Charlotte?

01:16.413 --> 01:17.478
A hot girl.

01:17.480 --> 01:19.147
Who's none of
your business.

01:19.149 --> 01:20.848
She's just a friend.

01:20.850 --> 01:22.083
Well... what kind of friend?

01:22.085 --> 01:24.085
She just texted you
like 12 times.

01:24.087 --> 01:25.453
All right, we like to talk.

01:25.455 --> 01:26.888
Okay.

01:26.890 --> 01:28.456
So she's that kind of friend.

01:28.458 --> 01:29.957
What's that mean?

01:29.959 --> 01:31.659
You know,
a friend who wants to be

01:31.661 --> 01:33.227
more than a friend
kind of friend.

01:33.229 --> 01:36.898
Well, actually,
I'd like to ask her out.

01:36.900 --> 01:38.533
Like a date?

01:38.535 --> 01:39.801
Pretty sure that's
what it's called

01:39.803 --> 01:41.235
when you go out with a girl.

01:41.237 --> 01:42.704
I... yeah, I mean, do you want

01:42.706 --> 01:44.706
to ask her out
on a date, for real?

01:44.708 --> 01:46.607
I mean, I was thinking about it,

01:46.609 --> 01:49.277
but I just don't know
what to do if she says no.

01:49.279 --> 01:51.045
If she says no, you just...

01:51.047 --> 01:53.081
you know, find yourself
another Charlotte.

01:53.083 --> 01:55.750
No way.
There's no one else like her.

01:55.752 --> 01:56.918
Yeah, I get that.

01:56.920 --> 01:58.152
All right, go ahead and eat.

02:02.658 --> 02:04.659
Great.

02:04.661 --> 02:06.127
Hey.
Hey.

02:06.129 --> 02:08.628
Our son likes a girl.

02:08.631 --> 02:09.896
Charlotte Lewis?

02:09.899 --> 02:12.033
You knew already?

02:12.035 --> 02:14.001
Well, he's had the hots
for her forever.

02:14.003 --> 02:16.804
Why am I always the last one
to know everything around here?

02:16.806 --> 02:17.972
Well...

02:17.974 --> 02:20.274
I got called in early to work.

02:20.276 --> 02:21.509
You mind driving
the boys to school?

02:21.511 --> 02:22.777
Of course not, but
we were supposed

02:22.779 --> 02:24.879
to look at tiles for the
bathroom this morning.

02:24.881 --> 02:26.781
Have fun with that.

02:29.651 --> 02:31.352
Good morning.
Is it?

02:31.354 --> 02:33.254
Deputy Commissioner Moore
and Lieutenant Gormley...

02:33.256 --> 02:34.589
Are already here.

02:34.591 --> 02:36.624
Morning, Frank.
How you doing there, Commissioner?

02:36.626 --> 02:37.959
So far, so good.

02:37.961 --> 02:39.327
Then let's get to it.

02:39.329 --> 02:41.596
I've been fielding calls
all morning, Frank.

02:41.598 --> 02:42.997
The <i>Times</i>
wants a quote

02:42.999 --> 02:44.665
on the mayor's statement
that he's putting

02:44.667 --> 02:46.100
a hiring freeze
on police officers.

02:46.102 --> 02:47.301
Shortsighted,

02:47.303 --> 02:49.837
dangerous
and just plain asinine.

02:49.839 --> 02:51.506
So, "No comment
at this time""

02:51.508 --> 02:53.641
Exactly.
That's how you guys do that?

02:53.643 --> 02:54.675
Next.
People magazine

02:54.677 --> 02:56.644
wants to schedule
an interview...

02:56.646 --> 02:57.779
No.

02:57.781 --> 02:59.847
But they...
No.

02:59.849 --> 03:02.583
This is a list of proposed
candidates for Medal Day.

03:02.585 --> 03:03.518
Also, I...

03:03.520 --> 03:05.052
Why wasn't I given a heads-up

03:05.054 --> 03:07.388
that Detective Reagan
is on this list?

03:11.026 --> 03:13.728
Um... I didn't think you
needed a heads-up.

03:13.730 --> 03:16.297
Well, I know for a fact
Lieutenant Carver

03:16.299 --> 03:19.333
and Detective Reagan
got off to a rocky start.

03:19.335 --> 03:21.135
Now she's recommending
a Medal for Valor?

03:21.137 --> 03:22.336
What the hell?

03:22.338 --> 03:24.272
Well...

03:24.274 --> 03:26.073
The mayor wants an update on

03:26.075 --> 03:27.008
the heightened
security measures

03:27.010 --> 03:28.509
for the
St. Patrick's Day parade.

03:28.511 --> 03:30.812
Does he, in addition
to a hiring freeze?

03:30.814 --> 03:32.847
Well, he doesn't look at them
side by side.

03:32.849 --> 03:36.584
Tell him I can spare three
meter maids and a bullhorn.

03:40.322 --> 03:42.323
- Sir, you have to leave.
- I get robbed,

03:42.325 --> 03:44.559
and you're telling me I
got to leave my own house?

03:44.561 --> 03:47.628
That's because your house is now
a crime scene, Mr. Bianco.

03:47.630 --> 03:48.763
Detective Reagan and Baez.

03:48.765 --> 03:50.865
In order for us to
do our jobs, we need

03:50.867 --> 03:52.600
to be able to get
crime scene in the house

03:52.602 --> 03:53.734
to figure out what happened.

03:53.736 --> 03:55.903
I already told you guys
what happened.

03:57.373 --> 03:58.739
My wife is so upset.

03:58.741 --> 04:01.442
Nick, let's just go.
Come on.

04:01.444 --> 04:03.311
I imagine so, when her husband

04:03.313 --> 04:04.979
kills a guy
right in her own house.

04:04.981 --> 04:07.548
Guy breaks into my home--
what am I supposed to do?

04:07.550 --> 04:09.851
Do you have a
license for the gun?

04:09.853 --> 04:11.152
I got a permit.

04:11.154 --> 04:12.587
I own my own business.

04:12.589 --> 04:14.021
I carry cash sometimes.

04:14.023 --> 04:15.456
You think that's what
he was after?

04:15.458 --> 04:17.158
How am I supposed to know?

04:19.161 --> 04:21.161
Do you know the guy
that broke into the house?

04:21.164 --> 04:22.597
No.

04:22.599 --> 04:25.099
Why do I feel like I'm the one
did something wrong here?

04:25.101 --> 04:26.267
I'm the victim.

04:26.269 --> 04:28.202
You think of anyone
who would want to kill you?

04:28.204 --> 04:30.705
Can I think of anyone
who might want to kill me?

04:30.707 --> 04:32.506
How much time do you have?

04:42.451 --> 04:43.985
Erin Reagan.

04:43.987 --> 04:45.519
I'm Justin Taylor.

04:45.521 --> 04:47.088
Sorry. Should I know you?

04:47.090 --> 04:49.390
I'm the lawyer who filed
for the 440 motion

04:49.392 --> 04:51.459
on behalf of my client--
for a retrial.

04:51.461 --> 04:52.960
Uh, your client?

04:52.962 --> 04:54.161
Uh, Suzanne Taylor.

04:54.163 --> 04:56.530
You put her away
12 years ago-- unjustly.

04:56.532 --> 04:58.833
Well, I'm going to have
to look up that case.

04:58.835 --> 05:01.435
Uh, the-the murder of a 24-hour
convenience store clerk,

05:01.437 --> 05:03.471
up in Morningside Heights.

05:04.373 --> 05:06.374
She was sentenced
to 15 years

05:06.376 --> 05:07.708
for a crime that
she didn't commit.

05:07.710 --> 05:09.343
I'm petitioning
for a retrial

05:09.345 --> 05:10.711
because she's innocent.

05:11.546 --> 05:13.180
And how do you know that?

05:14.349 --> 05:16.317
Because she's my mother.

